analysis: The documents all pertain to the establishment, modification, or expansion of wildlife refuges, primarily for migratory birds, under the authority of the President of the United States and the Migratory Bird Conservation Act. They describe specific land areas, often including detailed surveys and legal descriptions, that are being set aside for the Department of Agriculture or Interior to manage as refuges. Many orders include prohibitions against hunting, trapping, and disturbing wildlife within the refuge boundaries.
title: Migratory Bird and Wildlife Refuges
